    "created_at": "2025-02-11T09:26:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-02-11T09:26:50Z",
    "body": "FWIW, I'm using `STARSHIP_CONFIG` to use a trimmed down version of the configuration for certain paths:\n\n```zsh\nslim-starship() {\n  if [[ \"$PWD\" =~ ^/remote/ ]] || [[ \"$PWD\" =~ ^/mnt/ ]]; then\n    export STARSHIP_CONFIG=\"$HOME/.config/starship_slim.toml\"\n  else\n    unset STARSHIP_CONFIG\n  fi\n}\nadd-zsh-hook precmd slim-starship\n```\n\nWorks well enough for me.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
